Sentencas: A simple fabrication process for a 3D porous nickel anode for a thin film solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is developed.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: The 3D porous nickel anode is fabricated using a metal/proppant mixing method followed by pressing and heat treatment.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: The anode bulk possesses a high porosity which is required for efficient delivery of fuel to the cell.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: Following fabrication, the anode's surface is processed by means of mechanical, chemical, and ion etching to minimize surface roughness and reduce the surface pore size allowing for the deposition of a high quality, pore-free, thin electrolyte.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: Yttria-stabilized zirconia is used for the thin film electrolyte layer followed by deposition of a thin film La-0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-d cathode layer to complete the thin film SOFC.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: The fabricated cell performs with a very stable output power of 130 mW cm(-2) at temperatures of the order of 450 degrees C.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications

Sentencas: This anode is not only easy to shape, weld, and recycle but is also very economic.
Titulo: 3D Porous Nickel Anode for Low Temperature Thin Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Applications
